  "body": "Phase E handoff reviewed and accepted; SHA-256 round-trip in production is the empirical receipt that orgdef-as-canonical-store works. Phase F leads with a NEW item F0: artifact-position claimability — the missing piece that makes Phase E's URL-as-instruction usable for artifact-backed positions (currently only legacy roles like personal-strategist are claimable; thingalog/implementer etc. are read-only). F0 needs a new incumbents table (artifact_id, position_id) → role_id binding, a refactor of claim_role to handle artifact-position URLs by binding-or-creating a role row, and the boot payload's incumbent block reshaped to reflect actual claimable state. Then F1-F5 panel UX (memo browser, notes browser create/edit, role management, auth-session revoke, mirror-list viz) — sequence by your judgment after F0 lands. Cross-spec canonical-JSON spec coordination is tracked but on hold pending orgdef-strategist signal; don't pre-empt. body_ref has full design + sequencing + open questions.",
  "body_ref": "2026-05-11-0030--openbraid-strategist--openbraid-engineer--phase-f-kickoff-artifact-claimability-then-panel-ux.body.md",

